JOB ANNOUNCEMENT

Senior Political Reporter, Federal Policy/Capitol Hill

Rewire.News (www.rewire.news) is a nonprofit journalism organization devoted to publishing evidence-based news, analysis, commentary, and investigative reporting on health, rights, and justice. Our work is based on the core role of journalism in a democratic society: to foster public knowledge and dispel misinformation on issues more commonly shrouded in misinformation and ideology. Rewire.News is an independent 501(c)(3) and an equal opportunity employer; we encourage applications from qualified individuals of all races, ethnic groups, and genders.

POSITION DESCRIPTION

The Senior Political Reporter plays a critical role on our growing team. This position works closely with the editor-in-chief and the senior editorial team to ensure timely, accurate, and aggressive coverage of Congress, including legislation and federal policy issues affecting the economic, social, and health prospects of diverse populations of women, people of color, immigrants, youth, and LGBTQ people. The ideal candidate is a fearless, self-motivated, aggressive reporter who can identify the best stories for analysis and reporting; adept at establishing sources; devoted to being first to break stories; and has an excellent sense of priorities. The candidate can demonstrate an excellent track record of working quickly and on deadline to produce the highest quality news and analysis.

The Senior Political Reporter will be responsible for:

* As-needed breaking news and analysis of federal law and policy on Capitol Hill and the administration; the budget; abortion; contraception; Title X and family planning funding and policy; HIV and AIDS; and issues affecting the health and economic prospects of immigrant women, women of color, LGBTQ communities, and youth.

* Seeking out the stories or angles on stories others are not telling;

* Establishing and cultivating key contacts in Congress and relevant agencies;

* Attendance at key hearings and press conferences;

* Interviews with key policymakers and occasional profiles of legislators and policymakers in and outside the administration;

* Devotion to in-depth knowledge of legislation and policy and to getting the facts straight;

* Identifying and getting out front on stories that must be covered and connecting with the right people to do so;

* Working daily with the Rewire.News team to ensure smooth communications on current priorities - collaboration with other writers and columnists as necessary;

* Other duties and projects as assigned and as the site grows.

QUALIFICATIONS

The ideal candidate for this position demonstrates:

* Three (3) or more years of demonstrable reporting experience;

* Excellent writing and interpersonal communication skills, including the ability to write well on deadline while adhering to style;

* Excellent news judgment and the ability to find and prioritize stories;

* Proven experience in establishing contacts and cultivating sources;

* An understanding of online spaces and publications as well as of Twitter, Facebook, and other social media sites;

* Knowledge of and commitment to reproductive and sexual health and justice issues;

* Ability to work independently as well as participate on a team;

* Demonstrated experience as a disciplined self-starter who can set and achieve goals and is comfortable working remotely;

* Ability to take direction and critique;

* Willingness and ability, when necessary, to work evenings and weekends to cover a story;

* Ability to work quickly and effectively in a fast-paced environment, including multitasking (a critical aspect of this position);

* Creativity, idea sharing, and the ability to deliver great work with ease and grace;

* A sense of humor is highly desired!

LOCATION

Rewire.News is a virtual organization. Candidates for this position must, however, be able and willing to be present on Capitol Hill, and therefore be resident in the DC Metro Area. They must also have a home or other location with secure Internet access from which to work.

COMPENSATION

Rewire.News offers competitive compensation and a generous benefits package that includes a 401(k) plan with employer contributions; health and dental insurance; flexible spending accounts; vacation and sick leave; and employer-paid life insurance, AD&D, STD and LTD.

Salary range: sixties to high eighties, depending on demonstrated experience, skills, and seniority.
